        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 6:02PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 602 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Amherst to 12 miles southeast of
Highland Center, or extending from 8 miles northeast of Holyoke to
16 miles southwest of Holyoke, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Holyoke, Amherst, Pleasant Valley and Sixteen-Mile Corner.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
